| {{WP:RSPUSES|nndb.com}}

|- class="s-gr" id="NPR"
| [[NPR]] <small>(National Public Radio)</small> {{WP:RSPSHORTCUT|WP:RSPNPR}}
| {{WP:RSPSTATUS|gr}}
| [[WP:Reliable sources/Noticeboard/Archive 139#NPR reference in War On Women|1]] [[WP:Reliable sources/Noticeboard/Archive 149#NPR religion program claim from Judy Valente about membership estimate from Christian Science church|2]] [[WP:Reliable sources/Noticeboard/Archive 292#NPR|3]] [[WP:Reliable sources/Noticeboard/Archive 322#Using an NPR report in the article Misinformation related to the COVID-19 pandemic|4]] [[WP:Reliable sources/Noticeboard/Archive 448#Is NPR a reliable source?|5]]
| {{WP:RSPLAST|2024}}
| There is consensus that NPR, an American public service broadcaster, is generally reliable for news and statements of fact. NPR's [[WP:RSOPINION|opinion pieces]] should only be used with [[WP:INTEXT|attribution]].
| {{WP:RSPUSES|npr.org}}

|- class="s-d" id="Occupy Democrats"
