| {{WP:RSPLAST|2021}}
| The Victims of Communism Memorial Foundation is an American [[anti-communist]] think tank and [[WP:SPS|blog]], considered to be an unreliable source due to misinformation and a generally poor reputation for fact checking and accuracy.
| {{WP:RSPUSES|victimsofcommunism.org}}

|- class="s-gr" id="The Village Voice"
| data-sort-value="Village Voice" | ''[[The Village Voice]]''
| {{WP:RSPSTATUS|gr}}
| [[WP:Reliable_sources/Noticeboard/Archive_43#Village_Voice_Editorial_"Swift_Boat_Swill"|1]] [[WP:Reliable_sources/Noticeboard/Archive_50#Self-described_guide_to_"alternative_opinion"|2]] [[WP:Reliable_sources/Noticeboard/Archive_53#Is_village_voice_a_reliable_source|3]] [[WP:Reliable_sources/Noticeboard/Archive_159#"Consortium%20News"%20at%20October%20Surprise%20conspiracy%20theory|4]] [[WP:Reliable_sources/Noticeboard/Archive_193#American%20Mercury%20et%20al|5]] [[WP:Reliable_sources/Noticeboard/Archive_186#Is%20The%20Bay%20Magazine%20usable?|6]] [[WP:Reliable_sources/Noticeboard/Archive_222#All%20newspapers%20that%20publish%20in%20tabloid%20format%20are%20not%20reliable%20sources?|7]] [[WP:Reliable_sources/Noticeboard/Archive_349#Boston_Phoenix|8]] [[WP:Reliable_sources/Noticeboard/Archive_432#NYC%20Local%20Journalism,%20the%20Israeli%20Press%20&%20coverage%20of%20pro-Palestine%20Protesting|9]]
| {{WP:RSPLAST|2024}}
| There is consensus among editors that ''The Village Voice'' is generally reliable. It is an [[alternative newspaper|alternative]] [[newsweekly]] that has received multiple [[Pulitzer Prizes]].
| {{WP:RSPUSES|villagevoice.com}}

|- class="s-gr" id="Vogue"
| ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'' {{WP:RSPSHORTCUT|WP:VOGUE}}
| {{WP:RSPSTATUS|gr}}
| [[WP:Reliable sources/Noticeboard/Archive 30#Problematic source on Hak Ja Han|1]] [[WP:Reliable sources/Noticeboard/Archive 81#Sources with Quotes|2]] [[WP:Reliable sources/Noticeboard/Archive 83#Quote in News Article as a Source|3]] [[WP:Reliable sources/Noticeboard/Archive 237#It's time to talk about biography.com generally|4]]
| {{WP:RSPLAST|2018}}
| ''Vogue'' is considered generally reliable. Potentially contentious statements made by ''Vogue'' interview subjects can be [[WP:INTEXT|attributed]] to the individual.
