| {{WP:RSPSTATUS|gr}}
| [[WP:Reliable sources/Noticeboard/Archive 3#leaked documents?|1]] [[WP:Reliable sources/Noticeboard/Archive 79#Wired.com|2]] [[WP:Reliable sources/Noticeboard/Archive 103#wired.com and whosnews.usaweekend.com|3]] [[WP:Reliable sources/Noticeboard/Archive 109#Wired 1998|4]] [[WP:Reliable sources/Noticeboard/Archive 199#Wired magazine story and insistence by editors to follow apparent misrepresentation|5]] [[WP:Reliable sources/Noticeboard/Archive 200#Wired re: time travel|6]] [[Wikipedia:Reliable sources/Noticeboard/Archive 489#WIRED admitting to publishing stories without fact checking them, knowingly doesn't publish a retraction until outed months after the fact|7]]<br> [[Wikipedia talk:WikiProject Video games/Sources/Archive 4#Wired|A]]
